{"title_page": "Jonathan Casillas", "text_new": "{{short description|American football linebacker}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL player\n|name= Jonathan Casillas\n|image=Jonathan Casillas Saints parade.jpg\n|caption= Casillas at the 2010 Super Bowl parade in New Orleans\n|current_team = Free Agent\n|number=\n|position=[[Linebacker]]\n|birth_date={{birth date and age|1987|6|3|mf=y}}\n|birth_place=[[Jersey City, New Jersey]]\n|height_ft = 6\n|height_in = 1\n|weight_lbs = 227\n|high_school = [[New Brunswick High School|New Brunswick (NJ)]]\n|college=[[Wisconsin Badgers football|Wisconsin]]\n|undraftedyear=2009\n|pastteams=\n*[[New Orleans Saints]] ({{NFL Year|2009}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2012}})\n*[[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] ({{NFL Year|2013}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2014}})\n*[[New England Patriots]] ({{NFL Year|2014}})\n*[[New York Giants]] ({{NFL Year|2015}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2017}})\n|status=\n|highlights=\n* 2\u00d7 [[Super Bowl]] champion ([[Super Bowl XLIV|XLIV]], [[Super Bowl XLIX|XLIX]])\n|statweek=\n|statseason=2017\n|statlabel1=[[Tackle (football move)|Total tackles]]\n|statvalue1=385\n|statlabel2=[[Quarterback sacks|Sacks]]\n|statvalue2=6.5\n|statlabel3=[[Fumble|Forced fumbles]]\n|statvalue3=3\n|statlabel4=[[Fumble|Fumble recoveries]]\n|statvalue4=2\n|statlabel5=[[Interceptions]]\n|statvalue5=1\n|nfl=CAS320904\n}}\n'''Jonathan Casillas''' (born June 3, 1987) is an [[American football]] [[linebacker]] currently a free agent. He played [[high school football]] at [[New Brunswick High School]] and [[college football]] at [[Wisconsin Badgers football|Wisconsin]]. He is of [[Puerto Ricans|Puerto Rican]] and [[African-American]] ancestry.\n\n==College career==\nHe played [[college football]] at [[Wisconsin Badgers football|Wisconsin]].\n\n==Professional career==\n{{NFL predraft\n|    height ft = 6\n|    height in = 1\n|       weight = 238\n|         dash = 4.50\n|    ten split = \n| twenty split = \n|      shuttle = \n|   cone drill = \n|     vertical = \n|     broad ft = \n|     broad in = \n|        bench = 24\n|    wonderlic = \n|     arm span = \n|    hand span = \n|         note = All values from [[NFL combine]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nflcombineresults.com/playerpage.php?f=Jonathan&l=Casillas&i=8164 |title=NFL Combine Results: Jonathan Casillas |website=NFL.com |access-date=September 28, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n===New Orleans Saints===\nHe went undrafted in the [[2009 NFL Draft]], but was later signed as a free agent.<ref>[http://www.saintsgab.com/2009/05/06/will-the-saints-find-gold-in-the-2009-undrafted-free-agents-class/ Will the Saints Find Gold in the 2009 Undrafted Free Agents Class?]</ref> Casillas was coming off surgery from a knee injury and was only a participant in the bench press at the [[NFL Combine]].\n\nIn [[Super Bowl XLIV]], he was officially credited with recovering the Saints's third-quarter onside kick to start the second half en route to their 31-17 victory over the [[Indianapolis Colts]].<ref>https://sports.yahoo.com/nfl/boxscore?gid=20100207011&page=plays</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2010/02/08/sports/football/08lapointe.html \"Saints Coach\u2019s Pair of Bold Bets: One Miss, One Turning Point\"], ''[[The New York Times]]'', Joe LaPointe February 8, 2010.</ref>\n\nCasillas was expected to take over as the Saints' starting weakside linebacker for the 2010 season.  However, he suffered a foot injury during the last game of the preseason, and he was placed on the [[injured reserve]] list, ending his 2010 season.<ref>[http://www.nola.com/saints/index.ssf/2010/09/saints_jonathan_casillas_heade.html \"New Orleans Saints' Jonathan Casillas out for the season\"], [[NOLA.com|The Times-Picayune]], September 4, 2010.</ref>\n\n===Tampa Bay Buccaneers===\nCasillas signed with the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] on March 13, 2013.<ref>[http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2013/03/13/jonathan-casillas-makes-the-jump-from-saints-to-bucs/ Jonathan Casillas makes the jump from Saints to Bucs]</ref>  He played in 12 games before being placed on injured reserve after suffering a knee injury.<ref>[http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2013/12/04/bucs-place-jonathan-casillas-on-injured-reserve/ \"Bucs place Jonathan Casillas on injured reserve\"], [[Profootballtalk.com]], December 4, 2013.</ref> On March 7, 2014, Casillas re-signed with the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] on a one-year deal.\n\n===New England Patriots===\nCasillas, along with a 2015 sixth-round draft pick, was traded to the [[New England Patriots]] on October 28, 2014, for the Patriots' 2015 fifth-round draft pick.\nOn February 1, 2015, he won his second [[Super Bowl ring]] when the Patriots defeated the [[Seattle Seahawks]], 28\u201324, in [[Super Bowl XLIX]].\n\n===New York Giants===\nOn March 10, 2015, Casillas signed a three-year, $10.5 million contract with the [[New York Giants]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Linebacker Jonathan Casillas signs four-year deal with Giants|url=http://www.nj.com/giants/index.ssf/2015/03/giants_sign_jonathan_casillas_to_four-year_deal_pe.html|publisher=nj.com|accessdate=March 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171207084012/http://www.giants.com/news-and-blogs/combine/article-1/Giants-sign-RB-Shane-Vereen-announce-Free-Agent-signings/38303cc8-4214-4e78-8dea-b31cb6e08630|title=Giants sign RB Shane Vereen; announce Free Agent signings|work=Giants.com|first=Michael|last=Eisen|date=March 11, 2015|accessdate=March 12, 2015}}</ref> Signed as a special teamer, Casillas emerged as a starter for the Giants midway through the 2015 season.\n\nIn 2016, Casillas played in all 16 games with 15 starts, recording a career-high 96 tackles.\n\nIn 2017, Casillas started eight games before being placed on injured reserve on December 6, 2017 after battling wrist and neck injuries.<ref>{{cite web|title=Giants\u2019 injury news: LB Jonathan Casillas to IR, WR Darius Powe promoted|url=https://www.bigblueview.com/2017/12/6/16743786/giants-injury-news-lb-jonathan-casillas-ir-wr-darius-powe-promoted-practice-squad|website=BigBlueView.com|date=December 6, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat}}\n*[http://www.neworleanssaints.com/team/roster/Jonathan-Casillas/4800065a-2bd6-4cd1-aeab-89105f7c5b40 New Orleans Saints bio]\n*[https://archive.is/20071119173817/http://www.uwbadgers.com/sport_news/fb/bios/bio.html?athid=5571&deptid=111 Wisconsin Badgers bio]\n\n{{Super Bowl XLIV}}\n{{Super Bowl XLIX}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Casillas, Jonathan}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Brunswick High School alumni]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Jersey City, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:American football linebackers]]\n[[Category:Wisconsin Badgers football players]]\n[[Category:New Orleans Saints players]]\n[[Category:Tampa Bay Buccaneers players]]\n[[Category:New England Patriots players]]\n[[Category:New York Giants players]]\n[[Category:Super Bowl champions]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American football linebacker}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL player\n|name= Jonathan Casillas\n|image=Jonathan Casillas Saints parade.jpg\n|caption= Casillas at the 2010 Super Bowl parade in New Orleans\n|current_team = Free Agent\n|number=\n|position=[[Linebacker]]\n|birth_date={{birth date and age|1987|6|3|mf=y}}\n|birth_place=[[Jersey City, New Jersey]]\n|height_ft = 6\n|height_in = 1\n|weight_lbs = 227\n|high_school = [[New Brunswick High School|New Brunswick (NJ)]]\n|college=[[Wisconsin Badgers football|Wisconsin]]\n|undraftedyear=2009\n|pastteams=\n*[[New Orleans Saints]] ({{NFL Year|2009}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2012}})\n*[[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] ({{NFL Year|2013}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2014}})\n*[[New England Patriots]] ({{NFL Year|2014}})\n*[[New York Giants]] ({{NFL Year|2015}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2017}})\n|status=\n|highlights=\n* 2\u00d7 [[Super Bowl]] champion ([[Super Bowl XLIV|XLIV]], [[Super Bowl XLIX|XLIX]])\n|statweek=\n|statseason=2017\n|statlabel1=[[Tackle (football move)|Total tackles]]\n|statvalue1=385\n|statlabel2=[[Quarterback sacks|Sacks]]\n|statvalue2=6.5\n|statlabel3=[[Fumble|Forced fumbles]]\n|statvalue3=3\n|statlabel4=[[Fumble|Fumble recoveries]]\n|statvalue4=2\n|statlabel5=[[Interceptions]]\n|statvalue5=1\n|nfl=CAS320904\n}}\n'''Jonathan Casillas''' (born June 3, 1987) is an [[American football]] [[linebacker]] currently a free agent. He played [[high school football]] at [[New Brunswick High School]] and [[college football]] at [[Wisconsin Badgers football|Wisconsin]]. He is of [[Puerto Ricans|Puerto Rican]] and [[African-American]] ancestry.\n\n==College career==\nHe played [[college football]] at [[Wisconsin Badgers football|Wisconsin]].\n\n==Professional career==\n{{NFL predraft\n|    height ft = 6\n|    height in = 1\n|       weight = 238\n|         dash = 4.50\n|    ten split = \n| twenty split = \n|      shuttle = \n|   cone drill = \n|     vertical = \n|     broad ft = \n|     broad in = \n|        bench = 24\n|    wonderlic = \n|     arm span = \n|    hand span = \n|         note = All values from [[NFL combine]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nflcombineresults.com/playerpage.php?f=Jonathan&l=Casillas&i=8164 |title=NFL Combine Results: Jonathan Casillas |website=NFL.com |access-date=September 28, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n===New Orleans Saints===\nHe went undrafted in the [[2009 NFL Draft]], but was later signed as a free agent.<ref>[http://www.saintsgab.com/2009/05/06/will-the-saints-find-gold-in-the-2009-undrafted-free-agents-class/ Will the Saints Find Gold in the 2009 Undrafted Free Agents Class?]</ref> Casillas was coming off surgery from a knee injury and was only a participant in the bench press at the [[NFL Combine]].\n\nIn [[Super Bowl XLIV]], he was officially credited with recovering the Saints's third-quarter onside kick to start the second half en route to their 31-17 victory over the [[Indianapolis Colts]].<ref>https://sports.yahoo.com/nfl/boxscore?gid=20100207011&page=plays</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2010/02/08/sports/football/08lapointe.html \"Saints Coach\u2019s Pair of Bold Bets: One Miss, One Turning Point\"], ''[[New York Times]]'', Joe LaPointe February 8, 2010.</ref>\n\nCasillas was expected to take over as the Saints' starting weakside linebacker for the 2010 season.  However, he suffered a foot injury during the last game of the preseason, and he was placed on the [[injured reserve]] list, ending his 2010 season.<ref>[http://www.nola.com/saints/index.ssf/2010/09/saints_jonathan_casillas_heade.html \"New Orleans Saints' Jonathan Casillas out for the season\"], [[NOLA.com|The Times-Picayune]], September 4, 2010.</ref>\n\n===Tampa Bay Buccaneers===\nCasillas signed with the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] on March 13, 2013.<ref>[http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2013/03/13/jonathan-casillas-makes-the-jump-from-saints-to-bucs/ Jonathan Casillas makes the jump from Saints to Bucs]</ref>  He played in 12 games before being placed on injured reserve after suffering a knee injury.<ref>[http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2013/12/04/bucs-place-jonathan-casillas-on-injured-reserve/ \"Bucs place Jonathan Casillas on injured reserve\"], [[Profootballtalk.com]], December 4, 2013.</ref> On March 7, 2014, Casillas re-signed with the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] on a one-year deal.\n\n===New England Patriots===\nCasillas, along with a 2015 sixth-round draft pick, was traded to the [[New England Patriots]] on October 28, 2014, for the Patriots' 2015 fifth-round draft pick.\nOn February 1, 2015, he won his second [[Super Bowl ring]] when the Patriots defeated the [[Seattle Seahawks]], 28\u201324, in [[Super Bowl XLIX]].\n\n===New York Giants===\nOn March 10, 2015, Casillas signed a three-year, $10.5 million contract with the [[New York Giants]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Linebacker Jonathan Casillas signs four-year deal with Giants|url=http://www.nj.com/giants/index.ssf/2015/03/giants_sign_jonathan_casillas_to_four-year_deal_pe.html|publisher=nj.com|accessdate=March 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171207084012/http://www.giants.com/news-and-blogs/combine/article-1/Giants-sign-RB-Shane-Vereen-announce-Free-Agent-signings/38303cc8-4214-4e78-8dea-b31cb6e08630|title=Giants sign RB Shane Vereen; announce Free Agent signings|work=Giants.com|first=Michael|last=Eisen|date=March 11, 2015|accessdate=March 12, 2015}}</ref> Signed as a special teamer, Casillas emerged as a starter for the Giants midway through the 2015 season.\n\nIn 2016, Casillas played in all 16 games with 15 starts, recording a career-high 96 tackles.\n\nIn 2017, Casillas started eight games before being placed on injured reserve on December 6, 2017 after battling wrist and neck injuries.<ref>{{cite web|title=Giants\u2019 injury news: LB Jonathan Casillas to IR, WR Darius Powe promoted|url=https://www.bigblueview.com/2017/12/6/16743786/giants-injury-news-lb-jonathan-casillas-ir-wr-darius-powe-promoted-practice-squad|website=BigBlueView.com|date=December 6, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat}}\n*[http://www.neworleanssaints.com/team/roster/Jonathan-Casillas/4800065a-2bd6-4cd1-aeab-89105f7c5b40 New Orleans Saints bio]\n*[https://archive.is/20071119173817/http://www.uwbadgers.com/sport_news/fb/bios/bio.html?athid=5571&deptid=111 Wisconsin Badgers bio]\n\n{{Super Bowl XLIV}}\n{{Super Bowl XLIX}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Casillas, Jonathan}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Brunswick High School alumni]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Jersey City, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:American football linebackers]]\n[[Category:Wisconsin Badgers football players]]\n[[Category:New Orleans Saints players]]\n[[Category:Tampa Bay Buccaneers players]]\n[[Category:New England Patriots players]]\n[[Category:New York Giants players]]\n[[Category:Super Bowl champions]]\n", "name_user": "Alaney2k", "labe